Cricket South Africa elected Rihan Richards as their new president during an AGM this morning. Richards was acting president since the resignation of Chris Nendzani. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Cricket South Africa have elected Rihan Richards as their new president during an AGM on Saturday morning. Richards was acting president since the resignation of Chris Nendzani. READ: CSA controversy: Padding up for a new future A deadline was set for the organisation's new governance structure to come into effect in June. This followed an adoption of revisions to the Memorandum of Incorporation.